        "event": "Special Weather Statement",
        "headline": "Special Weather Statement issued April 6 at 8:55PM AKDT by NWS Fairbanks AK",
        "description": "A more active pattern brings snow and rain showers to much of the\nWest Coast and Western Interior late Monday which linger into\nWednesday. 1 to 3 inches of snow possible. Some areas may see\nperiods of mist and fog. Rain is most likely in the Lower Yukon\nand Upper Kuskokwim Valleys.\n\nA brief break is expected late Wednesday into early Thursday\nahead of another round of showery weather late Thursday into the\nweekend.",
